                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.512/437.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Vice Consul <persName type="from">Silliman</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico City</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-09-18">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 18, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>In a very satisfactory interview this afternoon with Ernesto Perusquia, Director
                    General of Stamp Tax Department, he stated that all questions regarding payment
                    of mining and other taxes by foreigners will be equitably adjusted at the
                    general stamp office in this city. Payments for the entire Republic may be made
                    here until further notice. The general office will make proper explanation to
                    the local offices. Correspondence with the general office is recommended to all
                    persons interested. The proper address is Direccion General del Timbre, City of
                    Mexico.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Silliman</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
